However, the loose contempt of court laws in South Africa mean newspapers have reported the story with what some might say has been a carefree attitude to objectivity and this has clearly worried Pistorius’s PR team.

As a result they have set up a Twitter account called @OscarHardTruth, which immediately claimed would set the record straight.

After it was created on Sunday, a tweet was posted that said: ‘As the trial approaches, many untruths half truths and versions of the truth have, and shall be spread across the world.' 

